The Chronicle With three episodes left before the curtain comes down on Season 2 of the Old Mutual Amazing Voices singing competition, it is all eyes on the four remaining groups — The Unveiled and Effect (Zimbabwe), Hush (South Africa) and 121 Selah (Nigeria) to see who will come out tops and win the US$100 000 prize money. <img class="wp-image-552950 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Effect1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Effect1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Effect1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Effect Tomorrow, one of the four groups will be eliminated from the show that is taking place at the Sun City Superbowl and being shown on DStv channels – Mzansi Magic and Zambezi Magic on Sunday’s at 5PM. <img class="wp-image-552952 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Hush.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Hush.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Hush-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Hush <img class="wp-image-552951 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/121-Selah.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/121-Selah.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/121-Selah-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Hush 